  "prompt_type": "cognitive",
  "prompt_text": "Calculate the probability of getting exactly 3 heads in 5 coin flips of a fair coin.",
  "response_text": "To calculate the probability of getting exactly 3 heads in 5 coin flips of a fair coin, we can use the binomial probability formula:\n\n\\[ P(X = k) = \\binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k} \\]\n\nwhere:\n- \\( n \\) is the number of trials (coin flips), which is 5 in this case.\n- \\( k \\) is the number of successful outcomes (heads), which is 3.\n- \\( p \\) is the probability of success on a single trial (getting heads), which is 0.5 for a fair coin.\n\nFirst, we calculate the binomial coefficient \\(\\binom{n}{k}\\):\n\n\\[ \\binom{5}{3} = \\frac{5!}{3!(5-3)!} = \\frac{5!}{3!2!} = \\frac{5 \\times 4}{2 \\times 1} = 10 \\]\n\nNext, we substitute the values into the binomial probability formula:\n\n\\[ P(X = 3) = \\binom{5}{3} (0.5)^3 (0.5)^{5-3} = 10 \\times (0.5)^3 \\times (0.5)^2 = 10 \\times 0.125 \\times 0.25 = 10 \\times 0.03125 = 0.3125 \\]\n\nSo, the probability of getting exactly 3 heads in 5 coin flips of a fair coin is \\(0.3125\\).\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 6\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
